Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_mutex_condition(25.10)                    report_mutex_condition(25.10)

Name
       report_mutex_condition - Reports mutex nets of a victim net

Syntax
       report_mutex_condition

        [-help]

        [-filename <<string>>]

        [-net <<string>>]

       Reports mutex nets of a victim net.

       When  this command is used, all the coupled nets that are participating
       in mutex for a victim will be reported. The coupled nets  will  be  re-
       ported as a group of mutex nets (user-defined). By default, all the mu-
       tex conditions are reported.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -filename <string>
              Specifies the name of the file that saves the command output re-
              sults.

       -net <string>
              Reports the coupled nets mutex to the specified net name.

              You  can  specify  multiple  net  names with multiple report_mu-
              tex_condition commands.

Examples
              * The following example shows mutex nets of a victim  net.  This
                report does not indicate the attackers not listed due to mutex
                command:

                Vic: Net1

                Attackers: Att1, Att2, Att3

                set_mutex_condition {Att1, Att2 }

                set_mutex_condition {Att2, Att3 }

                set_mutex_condition {Att1, Att3 }

                report_mutex_condition -net Net1 will report:

                - Victim Net: Net1

                Mutex groups:

                {Att1, Att2 },

                {Att2, Att3 },

                {Att1, Att3 }

              * The following example shows that if a coupled net is having LC
                chain  then the entire chain will be reported along with other
                mutex group nets:

                Vic: Net1

                Attackers: Att1, Att2, Att3

                Att1 chain: Agg1 Agg11 Agg111

                Att2 chain: Agg2 Agg22 Agg222

                Att3 chain: Agg3 Agg33 Agg333

                set_mutex_condition {Att1, Att2 }

                set_mutex_condition {Att2, Att3 }

                set_mutex_condition {Att1, Att3 }

                report_mutex_condition -net Net1 will report:

                - Victim Net: Net1

                Mutex groups:

                {{ Agg1 Agg11 Agg111 }, { Agg2 Agg22 Agg222}}

                {{ Agg2 Agg22 Agg222}, { Agg3 Agg33 Agg333}}

                {{ Agg1 Agg11 Agg111 }, { Agg3 Agg33 Agg333}}

